Robert Bates was charged with second-degree manslaughter in the shooting of Eric Harris on April 2 . 
  He appeared on the Today show on Friday to apologize to the family of the man he shot dead . 
  He said he accidentally pulled out his gun instead of his Taser during a botched undercover sting operation in Tulsa . 
  He was charged after he shot Harris dead during a chase . 
  Bates said the mix-up could have happened to anyone . 
 